Once you hit 55, it will be easier because you can kick stun.  Untill then taunt once or twice (2 times is generally safe incase the first one fails)<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>5. Regarding /shield, I know it protects the target, i.e. &quot;Jullianna begins to use Snapricot as a living shield&quot; but when shielded, what does that do?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Ok since you know how shield works (how to use it) I'll explain what it does.<br>
What it does is it takes 50% of the mobs damage that is being done to playerx(the one being beat on) and transfers  it to playery (you). When you get hit, it is 75% of the mobs total damage. So to say it simpler, the person you are shielding takes 50% less damage while you take 75% of the total mobs damage.<br>
<br>
<br>
Hope that helps.  <p>Binn da warlord</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=brutultarewmarr>Brutul Tarew Marr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Slayer of Whiners</span><br>  Posts: 1177<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/14/03 2:08:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2067.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://home.attbi.com/~laforman/45.jpg height=185 width=100></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Newbie Warrior looking for tips from the experts</span><hr size=1> 1) Your best upgrades are Fierce Heraldic Armor.  Expensive but very good.  Might look for a neck piece with some AC on it.<br>
<br>
2)  There are two reasons for using a fast mainhander.  The first one is that more hits (theoretically) equals more aggro, even if the hits are smaller, as long as the ratio is decent.  The second one is the fact that your mainhand gets a damage bonus added to every hit.  Since you get a bonus on every hit, a 10/20 weapon will do considerably more damage than a 20/40, even though the ratio is the same.  Offhand all that matters is ratio.  This becomes more of a factor as you level up because your damage bonus gets higher.  I don't know what Strikinone is talking about with the offhand becoming independent at higher levels, it is always independent.<br>
<br>
3)  You could write a book on pulling.  Every zone is different.  Just experiment with using a bow, proximity aggro, etc.  As someone else said, don't waste too much time getting singles if you have a CCer.  2 or 3 pulls are optimal if you have an enchanter in the group, single-pulling will just slow you down.<br>
<br>
4)  I personally hate standing there for 12 seconds taunting so most of the time I just run up and taunt-bash-disarm-attack.  If I hear a whining noise from the direction of the enchanter I'll start taunting two or more times.  If I am standing near a mezzed mob while fighting I will sometimes turn off attack for a second and get in a quick taunt on the mezzed mob and then go back to the one I'm tanking, just be careful not to break mez or that whining noise will start back up again.  During Enrage is a good time to get started Taunting, but almost no exp mobs enrage anymore.<br>
<br>
5)  I think Binnamer covered it.  Be sure you're standing real close to the person you're shielding or it won't work. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=325267">Brutul Vilesilencer</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
