Test Server</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=abividad>Abividad</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/14/03 2:11:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2067.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Newbie Warrior looking for tips from the experts</span><hr size=1> Your stuff looks good, no major horrors there. A couple of things for future upgrades<br>
<br>
On your weapons: The proc on the Snowchipper is a straight DD proc (120), so it won't add a whole lot of hate to you even when it goes off. A Frostbringer has a smaller DD (60) but also debuffs 12 AC off the mob, which tends to upset the mob a lot and make it pound you steadily, which is a good thing.<br>
<br>
You want the faster weapon in your mainhand so the damage bonus is added to more hits<br>
<br>
Being a Rallos worshipping Gnome, you get 2 great sets of armor that is player made, and you already have some nice tinkered stuff. Any of the Firece Heraldic Armor would be nice upgrades for wrists, neck, face, head, back or shoulders. They would add a lot of AC and Hit points. And of course, there is always Velious Quest armor depending on what faction you want to work on.<br>
<br>
I always taunt a couple of times. I remember reading some questions about the effectiveness of this, but I still do it to be better safe than sorry...can't hurt too much to wait 7 seconds before waking it up<br>
<br>
/Shield decreases the damage that the lightweight getting hit by the mob takes by 50% and you get hit for 75% of the mobs damage<br>
