<br>
proximity aggro; well; is kind of like when fighting a rooted mob. it hits the person closest to them. an example of this is Derakor the Vindicator; whos aggro is ( from what i have seen ) basically hit the closest person to him..i don't do much MT work anymore so things may have changed since when I was in those kind of roles.<br>
<br>
the 2H versus 1H weapon comprison question...the best way to answer that is &quot;whatever works for ya&quot;. as long as the mob keeps hitting you you're doing the right thing. if you can hold aggro with a 2Her than you'll definately cut down damage taken from mob DS's; ripostes; etc...yet if you can't hold the aggro with your 2Her than you'd be stuck doing the 1H thing which most often provides the most secure means of reliably holding aggro on you. and this all varies by level too; the higher level you are the more 2H weapons figure into your total DPS and damage bonus..<br>
<br>
as an example; at 61 now my most reliable weapon is my 2Her epic for pure aggro and taunt-value; yet for DPS my katana of pain and blue epic blade provide the most DPS for the job.<br>
<br>
the rest of the people here can sure steer you in more of a direct direction than i can; and they'd be sure to set ya straight if anything arises. on top of each of the forums here are sticky topics with a lot of basic facts and things that are most frequently asked. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
